text: Akhta () is a rural locality (a village) in Starokurmashevsky Selsoviet, Kushnarenkovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 73 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 9 km from Kushnarenkovo, 16 km from Starokurmashevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kushnarenkovsky District
title: Akhta, Republic of Bashkortostan
